channel.title: CVE Feed for Dell -- Wyse Management Suite
channel.description: The latest CVEs for Dell -- Wyse Management Suite

item.title: CVE-2022-29097|2024-09-16T16:22:41.350Z -- dell -- wyse%20management%20suite
item.description: Dell WMS 3.6.1 and below contains a Path Traversal vulnerability in Device API. A remote attacker could potentially exploit this vulnerability, to gain unauthorized read access to the files stored on the server filesystem, with the privileges of the running web application.

item.title: CVE-2019-3769|2024-09-16T16:43:16.810Z -- dell -- wyse%20management%20suite
item.description: Dell Wyse Management Suite versions prior to 1.4.1 contain a stored cross-site scripting vulnerability. A remote authenticated malicious user with low privileges could exploit this vulnerability to store malicious payload in the device heartbeat request. When victim users access the submitted data through their browsers, the malicious code gets executed by the web browser in the context of the vulnerable application.
